Oh Donald, when will you learn? You never count your chickens before they’re hatched. Also, don’t claim victory when the results are still unclear. The latest polls from Tuesday’s debate show mixed reactions. At first glance, they don’t look great for Hillary Clinton. According to focus groups from MSNBC and ABC, both had Donald Trump leading in Tuesday’s presidential debate. But were these groups representative of the broader electorate? According to focus groups at both MSNBC and ABC, Republican candidate Donald Trump narrowly beat Democratic nominee Hillary Clinton in the debate. At MSNBC, the group was split 14-6 in favor of Trump. And at ABC, pollster John Zogby’s group came out 13-7 in favor of the businessman. MSNBC’s group consisted of voters from Michigan, while Zogby’s group included voters from Ohio. Zogby, who followed the debate closely, noted that Trump gained momentum when he attacked Clinton on her email issue but struggled when defending his comments about Obama’s citizenship. However, what many aren’t reporting is that another poll showed Clinton winning 93% to 7%. Drudge poll… pic.twitter.com/UTCpTmMRbi — Greg Pollowitz (@GPollowitz) September 28, 2016  
